snippet.textDisplay:
Pusha T's song is nice but it isn't even near Drake's level. If you'd switch the words a bit, you'd see how boring the beat is. The only thing I actually liked was his voice and his style of rapping but he still has a lot to improve. Pusha got info out of Kanye probably (we don't know for sure) and then dissed Drake with it. Doesn't make him a good rapper more like a low person that digs in someone's dirty laundry. If he'd want to compete for real than let him create hits. Never heard his name before Drake beef. I'm still thankful for this video. It's interesting to see someone else's opinion on the video but I strongly disagree.
99% of people would've dissed the s**t out of Pusha T for coming for their families, the only reason Drake didn't do it (he said it in the interview) is because it might have escalated into some real gang fight or whatever and when you have real people around you, friends and family who are ready to stand for you even physically, you're responsible for them. Just look at other rappers and their friends getting into all kinds of troubles, people getting shot. Drake is much wiser than you give him credit for. He can't just sit in the interview and drop all the names, say all the details but you can read between the lines. Big wars have started from small confrontations.
